node.text:
[Correction] Expanding the facility into the outdoor area will allow the CEC to house a total of 4,400 patients, instead of another 4,400 as stated in the video.

The Changi Exhibition Centre isolation facility started receiving its first patients on Apr. 25, 2020.
Giving too much space to the patients
@snowbreeeze meaning dormitories patients will increase at lease few more thousands?
@rainbow05068 if only few thousand I feel its  a good outcome

The large numbers of dormitories' cases will be housed here.  Tanjong pagar also have another facility got 15k patients.  If we see more of these sites being set up we can expect much higher numbers incoming.
@whos_e.t the fact that the government is already doing something is not for you to complain about, be grateful. Those places are closed off due to covid-19 anyways, good to put them to use.
Ah ya , why government cannot reopen Dakota and Changi hospital! @mothershipsg
For every Singaporean and non-Singaporean brother and sister involved in this fight against Covid19, I thank you for your efforts. We will get through this together 🙏 #SGUNITED
Yup but people who’ve been sent to the expo have said they get 0 medical attention even when symptoms get worst saw in a video by the patient
